A secure project directory structure with subdirectories for docs, src, backups, and temp is created using mkdir -p command. File permissions are configured using chmod (750 for directories, 640 for files) and ownership is modified with chown to restrict unauthorized access. Umask value is set to 027 for enforcing stricter default permissions on newly created files within the workspace. All permission configurations, ownership details, and security explanations are documented in Project_Workspace_Report.txt.
